Tags:
  - Union-Identity=Mysterium Magnum=Silence
  - Invocation=The Word that God Utters
By: Eckhart
---
God is a word, an unspoken word. Augustine says： ‘All scripture is
vain.’ We say that God is unspoken, but he is unspeakable. Grant he is
somewhat; who can pronounce this word? None but the Word.
